          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "...now capable of change.",
                "italic": true
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Protagonist has undergone a transformation and uses their new abilities, knowledge, perspective, or an item they found, to vanquish the Villain / achieve their goal. Their c"
              },
              {
                "text": "hange must be made visual, often with a final showdown. This is t"
              },
              {
                "text": "he resolution of the story"
              },
              {
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create a final showdown – demonstrate how the Protagonist and other major characters have transformed from the beginning of the story (e.g. stronger, more courageous, more capable)."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Close the circle – show that the Protagonist, "
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "having emerged victorious,"
                  },
                  {
                    "text": " is once again in their normal world and ready for the next challenge which presents itself. "
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Example: The Protagonist and Allies lead the villagers in an attack, killing some of the loggers. The Allies hold the remaining logging crew at bay while the Protagonist faces off against their leader, causing grievous wounds. The loggers realize the cost of remaining in the village is too steep and agree to vacate the lands. The Protagonist has thus transformed from a passive protector of the lands to one who is willing to use force."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 3 makes up the final 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "This step occurs around the 85 - 87% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
