          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "In this section of the narrative it becomes clear that something is not perfect in the Protagonist's world – they have some Need (internal or external) which introduces the inciting incident that propels the Protagonist into the story. The Need must be vital so that there is no choice but to Go and deal with it."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Introduce the Protagonist's external and/or internal Need(s). The external Need is often a desire to change or achieve something, while the internal Need may be courage, respect, patience, love, or humility."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Present the inciting incident which propels the Protagonist out of their Zone of Comfort."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "list-item"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Example: Loggers arrive and threaten the Protagonist's village and food source. The Protagonist needs to stop the loggers to protect their home."
